headline: Xcel Energy's quarterly profit boosted by rate hikes, rising power demand
summary: Xcel was able to bring in more revenue through regulator-approved rate hikes in the quarter, helping it cover the costs of upgrading the grid, building new power sources and funding other major projects.  Utilities have been adding billions of dollars to their capital expenditure budgets as they field massive requests for new power capacity from new data centers needed for artificial intelligence technologies.  CEO Bob Frenzel said Xcel made "considerable progress" during the quarter on investments to strengthen system reliability and serve "unprecedented growth in electric demand."
